{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-page-jsx","path":"/react/chart/docs/guides/stacked-series/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h1 id=\"react-chart---stacked-series\"><a href=\"#react-chart---stacked-series\" aria-label=\"react chart   stacked series permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>React Chart - Stacked Series</h1>\n<p>The Chart component can collect line, spline, area and bar series in stacks. Stacked series require the <code class=\"language-text\">Stack</code> plugin.</p>\n<h2 id=\"basic-setup\"><a href=\"#basic-setup\" aria-label=\"basic setup permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Basic Setup</h2>\n<p>Add the <code class=\"language-text\">Stack</code> plugin to draw several bar series side-by-side as shown in the following example:</p>\n<p>.embedded-demo({ \"path\": \"chart-basic/band-axis\", \"showThemeSelector\": true })</p>\n<p>Also, specify the <code class=\"language-text\">stacks</code> property to draw series one under another:</p>\n<p>.embedded-demo({ \"path\": \"chart-basic/bar-line\", \"showThemeSelector\": true })</p>\n<h2 id=\"specify-series-order-and-offset\"><a href=\"#specify-series-order-and-offset\" aria-label=\"specify series order and offset permalink\" class=\"anchor\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Specify Series Order and Offset</h2>\n<p>The <code class=\"language-text\">Stack</code> plugin allows you to customize the series order and offset. In the following example, a stacked area series is used to create a streamgraph. Order and offset values are calculated by calling the <a href=\"https://github.com/d3/d3-shape/blob/master/README.md\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><code class=\"language-text\">d3-shape</code></a> library. Then, these values are passed to the <code class=\"language-text\">Stack</code> plugin's <code class=\"language-text\">order</code> and <code class=\"language-text\">offset</code> properties.</p>\n<p>.embedded-demo({ \"path\": \"chart-basic/streamgraph\", \"showThemeSelector\": true })</p>","fields":{"technology":"react/chart","section":"docs"},"frontmatter":{"title":""}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"react/chart/docs/guides/stacked-series/"}},"staticQueryHashes":["3159585216","3662068265"]}